    <item>
      <title>Overview</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/overview/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/overview/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Embedding Ferret means importing the &lt;code&gt;github.com/MontFerret/ferret/v2&lt;/code&gt; module and using its Go API to compile and execute FQL queries inside your own application.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The host application stays in control: it decides which functions are available, which parameters are passed in, which standard library groups are loaded, and which modules extend the runtime. Scripts written in FQL describe the extraction, transformation, or automation logic without needing access to the rest of the application.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Getting Started</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/getting-started/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/getting-started/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;getting-started&#34;&gt;Getting Started&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This page walks through installing Ferret as a Go dependency, running a query, and working with the result.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;installation&#34;&gt;Installation&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Add the module to your project:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor terminal-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;terminal-1-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;go get github.com/MontFerret/ferret/v2&lt;/textarea&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;terminal&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;terminal-1-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;pre id=&#34;terminal-1-content&#34; class=&#34;terminal-body&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-prompt&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;terminal-command&#34;&gt;go get github.com/MontFerret/ferret/v2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-1-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#terminal-1-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;            const terminalContent = copyClipboardEl.value;&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy terminal commands to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(terminalContent)&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy terminal commands&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;running-a-query&#34;&gt;Running a query&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The simplest way to execute a query is &lt;code&gt;engine.Run&lt;/code&gt;. It compiles the source, runs it in a fresh session, and returns the encoded output.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Custom Functions</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/custom-functions/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/custom-functions/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;custom-functions&#34;&gt;Custom Functions&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Custom functions let the host application expose Go logic to FQL scripts. Functions can be registered individually or organized into namespaces.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;registering-functions&#34;&gt;Registering functions&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The most direct way to add functions is &lt;code&gt;WithFunctionsRegistrar&lt;/code&gt;. The callback receives a &lt;code&gt;runtime.Namespace&lt;/code&gt; where you register functions by arity:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor is-readonly is-auto-height&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;code-8-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;example.go&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-meta&#34;&gt;read-only&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;code-8-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-8-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; data-auto-height=&#34;true&#34;&gt;engine, err := ferret.New(&#xA;    ferret.WithFunctionsRegistrar(func(ns runtime.Namespace) {&#xA;        ns.Function().A0().Add(&amp;#34;NOW_UNIX&amp;#34;, func(ctx context.Context) (runtime.Value, error) {&#xA;            return runtime.NewInt(int(time.Now().Unix())), nil&#xA;        })&#xA;&#xA;        ns.Function().A1().Add(&amp;#34;DOUBLE&amp;#34;, func(ctx context.Context, arg runtime.Value) (runtime.Value, error) {&#xA;            n, err := runtime.CastArg[runtime.Int](arg, 0)&#xA;            if err != nil {&#xA;                return nil, err&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            return runtime.NewInt(int(n * 2)), nil&#xA;        })&#xA;    }),&#xA;)&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-8-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace\/theme\/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setUseWorker(false);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;golang&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-8-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-8-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy source to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(editor.getValue())&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy source&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;            function resizeAutoHeightEditor() {&#xA;                const lineHeight = editor.renderer.lineHeight || 21;&#xA;                const screenLines = Math.max(editor.session.getScreenLength(), 1);&#xA;                const nextHeight = Math.max(screenLines * lineHeight, 48);&#xA;&#xA;                editor.container.style.height = `${nextHeight}px`;&#xA;                editor.resize();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            editor.session.on(&#39;change&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            window.addEventListener(&#39;resize&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            resizeAutoHeightEditor();&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Scripts can then call these functions directly:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Host Values</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/host-values/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/host-values/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;host-values&#34;&gt;Host Values&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Host values let an embedding application expose Go-managed resources and objects to FQL scripts. This page covers how to implement them in Go. For the FQL perspective — what host values look like inside a script and which operations they support — see &lt;a href=&#34;https://ferretlang.org/docs/language/types/host/&#34;&gt;Host Values&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://ferretlang.org/docs/language/types/capabilities/&#34;&gt;Capability Types&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;when-to-implement-a-host-value&#34;&gt;When to implement a host value&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resource handle&lt;/strong&gt; — the Go object owns an external resource (database connection, file handle, HTTP client) whose lifecycle outlives a single function call.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lazy value&lt;/strong&gt; — the value materializes data only when accessed, avoiding upfront cost (cursor, paginated result set).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Domain object&lt;/strong&gt; — the value has rich behavior (property access, iteration, dispatch) that cannot be expressed as a plain array or object.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;External client&lt;/strong&gt; — the value wraps a Go client library and exposes its operations through FQL capabilities (query, dispatch, subscribe).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Controlled capabilities&lt;/strong&gt; — you want to expose only certain operations (read-only properties, no iteration) rather than giving scripts full access to the underlying data.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;choosing-the-right-mechanism&#34;&gt;Choosing the right mechanism&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;table&gt;&#xA;  &lt;thead&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Mechanism&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Best for&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Script sees&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Lifecycle&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/thead&gt;&#xA;  &lt;tbody&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Parameter&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Static data: strings, numbers, config, JSON-like structures&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;@name&lt;/code&gt; — a plain value&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Host sets before execution&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Function&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Stateless computation: hash, format, fetch&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;FN(args)&lt;/code&gt; → result&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;No state between calls&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Host value&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Stateful resource or behavioral object&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Variable with capabilities: &lt;code&gt;val.prop&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;FOR x IN val&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;QUERY ... IN val&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Host creates; runtime tracks &lt;code&gt;io.Closer&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Module&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Self-contained extension bundling functions + hooks&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Namespaced functions and values&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Module &lt;code&gt;Register&lt;/code&gt; + engine lifecycle hooks&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/tbody&gt;&#xA;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When in doubt, walk through these questions:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Parameters</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/parameters/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/parameters/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;parameters&#34;&gt;Parameters&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Parameters let the host application inject values into FQL queries. They are the primary way to pass dynamic data — user IDs, URLs, configuration values, thresholds — from Go into a script without string interpolation or query rewriting.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;fql-parameter-syntax&#34;&gt;FQL parameter syntax&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In FQL, parameters are referenced with the &lt;code&gt;@&lt;/code&gt; prefix:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor is-readonly is-auto-height&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;code-10-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;example.fql&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-meta&#34;&gt;read-only&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;code-10-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-10-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; data-auto-height=&#34;true&#34;&gt;LET result = @base_url &amp;#43; &amp;#34;/users/&amp;#34; &amp;#43; TO_STRING(@user_id)&#xA;RETURN result&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-10-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace\/theme\/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setUseWorker(false);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;fql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-10-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-10-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy source to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(editor.getValue())&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy source&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;            function resizeAutoHeightEditor() {&#xA;                const lineHeight = editor.renderer.lineHeight || 21;&#xA;                const screenLines = Math.max(editor.session.getScreenLength(), 1);&#xA;                const nextHeight = Math.max(screenLines * lineHeight, 48);&#xA;&#xA;                editor.container.style.height = `${nextHeight}px`;&#xA;                editor.resize();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            editor.session.on(&#39;change&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            window.addEventListener(&#39;resize&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            resizeAutoHeightEditor();&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;engine-level-parameters&#34;&gt;Engine-level parameters&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Parameters set on the engine apply as defaults to every session. Use these for values that rarely change — base URLs, API keys, environment names.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Configuration</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/configuration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/configuration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;configuration&#34;&gt;Configuration&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The engine accepts functional options that control which capabilities are available to scripts, how results are encoded, how execution is logged, and how concurrency is managed.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;standard-library&#34;&gt;Standard library&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;By default, the engine loads the full standard library. You can restrict it to a subset of groups or disable it entirely.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;available-groups&#34;&gt;Available groups&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;table&gt;&#xA;  &lt;thead&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Group&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Contents&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/thead&gt;&#xA;  &lt;tbody&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;Types&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Type checking and conversion functions&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;Strings&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;String manipulation&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;Math&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Mathematical operations&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;Collections&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Generic collection operations&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;DateTime&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Date and time functions&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;Arrays&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Array-specific operations&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;Objects&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Object-specific operations&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;IO&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Expands to &lt;code&gt;FS&lt;/code&gt; + &lt;code&gt;NET&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;FS&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;File system access&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;NET&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Network operations&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;Path&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;File path manipulation&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;Utils&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Utility functions&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;Testing&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Test assertion functions&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/tbody&gt;&#xA;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;selecting-groups&#34;&gt;Selecting groups&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor is-readonly is-auto-height&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;code-10-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;example.go&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-meta&#34;&gt;read-only&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;code-10-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-10-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; data-auto-height=&#34;true&#34;&gt;// Full standard library (default)&#xA;ferret.New(&#xA;    ferret.WithStdlib(stdlib.Full()),&#xA;)&#xA;&#xA;// Everything except file system and network access&#xA;ferret.New(&#xA;    ferret.WithStdlib(stdlib.Safe()),&#xA;)&#xA;&#xA;// Only specific groups&#xA;ferret.New(&#xA;    ferret.WithStdlib(stdlib.Only(stdlib.Strings, stdlib.Math, stdlib.Arrays)),&#xA;)&#xA;&#xA;// Full minus specific groups&#xA;ferret.New(&#xA;    ferret.WithStdlib(stdlib.Full().Without(stdlib.IO, stdlib.Testing)),&#xA;)&#xA;&#xA;// No standard library at all&#xA;ferret.New(&#xA;    ferret.WithoutStdlib(),&#xA;)&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-10-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace\/theme\/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setUseWorker(false);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;golang&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-10-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-10-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy source to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(editor.getValue())&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy source&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;            function resizeAutoHeightEditor() {&#xA;                const lineHeight = editor.renderer.lineHeight || 21;&#xA;                const screenLines = Math.max(editor.session.getScreenLength(), 1);&#xA;                const nextHeight = Math.max(screenLines * lineHeight, 48);&#xA;&#xA;                editor.container.style.height = `${nextHeight}px`;&#xA;                editor.resize();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            editor.session.on(&#39;change&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            window.addEventListener(&#39;resize&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            resizeAutoHeightEditor();&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;stdlib.Safe()&lt;/code&gt; is equivalent to &lt;code&gt;stdlib.Full().Without(stdlib.IO)&lt;/code&gt; — it removes file system and network access while keeping everything else.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Value Encoders</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/value-encoders/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/value-encoders/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;value-encoders&#34;&gt;Value Encoders&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When a session finishes, Ferret encodes the result value into bytes using a codec selected by content type. The &lt;code&gt;Output&lt;/code&gt; struct carries the encoded bytes and their MIME type:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor is-readonly is-auto-height&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;code-11-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;example.go&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-meta&#34;&gt;read-only&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;code-11-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-11-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; data-auto-height=&#34;true&#34;&gt;output, err := session.Run(ctx)&#xA;if err != nil {&#xA;    log.Fatal(err)&#xA;}&#xA;&#xA;fmt.Println(output.ContentType) // &amp;#34;application/json&amp;#34;&#xA;fmt.Println(string(output.Content))&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-11-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace\/theme\/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setUseWorker(false);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;golang&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-11-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-11-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy source to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(editor.getValue())&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy source&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;            function resizeAutoHeightEditor() {&#xA;                const lineHeight = editor.renderer.lineHeight || 21;&#xA;                const screenLines = Math.max(editor.session.getScreenLength(), 1);&#xA;                const nextHeight = Math.max(screenLines * lineHeight, 48);&#xA;&#xA;                editor.container.style.height = `${nextHeight}px`;&#xA;                editor.resize();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            editor.session.on(&#39;change&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            window.addEventListener(&#39;resize&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            resizeAutoHeightEditor();&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;built-in-codecs&#34;&gt;Built-in codecs&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Two codecs are registered by default:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Programs</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/programs/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/programs/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;programs&#34;&gt;Programs&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A compiled Ferret query can be serialized into a binary artifact and loaded later without the compiler. This is useful for distributing pre-compiled queries, skipping compilation at runtime, or caching build output on disk.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;two-paths-to-a-plan&#34;&gt;Two paths to a Plan&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There are two ways to get a &lt;code&gt;Plan&lt;/code&gt; from the engine:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor is-readonly is-auto-height&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;code-11-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;example.go&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-meta&#34;&gt;read-only&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;code-11-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-11-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; data-auto-height=&#34;true&#34;&gt;// From FQL source — compiles and returns a plan&#xA;plan, err := engine.Compile(ctx, source.NewAnonymous(`RETURN 1 &amp;#43; 1`))&#xA;&#xA;// From a pre-compiled artifact — loads and returns a plan&#xA;plan, err := engine.Load(artifactBytes)&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-11-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace\/theme\/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setUseWorker(false);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;golang&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-11-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-11-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy source to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(editor.getValue())&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy source&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;            function resizeAutoHeightEditor() {&#xA;                const lineHeight = editor.renderer.lineHeight || 21;&#xA;                const screenLines = Math.max(editor.session.getScreenLength(), 1);&#xA;                const nextHeight = Math.max(screenLines * lineHeight, 48);&#xA;&#xA;                editor.container.style.height = `${nextHeight}px`;&#xA;                editor.resize();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            editor.session.on(&#39;change&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            window.addEventListener(&#39;resize&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            resizeAutoHeightEditor();&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Both produce the same &lt;code&gt;*Plan&lt;/code&gt; that you create sessions from and run. The difference is where the bytecode comes from: the compiler or a serialized artifact.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Modules &amp; Hooks</title>
      <link>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/modules/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ferretlang.org/docs/embedding/modules/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;modules--hooks&#34;&gt;Modules &amp;amp; Hooks&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Modules are self-contained extensions that bundle functions, parameters, codecs, and lifecycle hooks into a single registerable unit. Hooks let both modules and the host application react to events in the engine lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-module-interface&#34;&gt;The Module interface&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A module implements two methods:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor is-readonly is-auto-height&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;textarea id=&#34;code-6-copy-clipboard&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-clipboard&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-shell&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-header&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-title&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-dot&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span&gt;example.go&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-actions&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;span class=&#34;code-editor-meta&#34;&gt;read-only&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;                &lt;button id=&#34;code-6-copy-button&#34; class=&#34;copy button is-outlined is-light code-editor-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;code-editor-pane&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-6-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; data-auto-height=&#34;true&#34;&gt;type Module interface {&#xA;    Name() string&#xA;    Register(Bootstrap) error&#xA;}&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-6-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace\/theme\/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setUseWorker(false);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;golang&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;            const copyBtn = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-6-copy-button&#39;);&#xA;            const copyClipboardEl = document.querySelector(&#39;#code-6-copy-clipboard&#39;);&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextWithFallback(content) {&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.value = content;&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.focus();&#xA;                copyClipboardEl.select();&#xA;&#xA;                if (!document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)) {&#xA;                    throw new Error(&#39;Could not copy source to the clipboard&#39;);&#xA;                }&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            function copyTextToClipboard(content) {&#xA;                if (navigator.clipboard &amp;&amp; navigator.clipboard.writeText) {&#xA;                    return navigator.clipboard.writeText(content).catch(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;                    });&#xA;                }&#xA;&#xA;                copyTextWithFallback(content);&#xA;&#xA;                return Promise.resolve();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            copyBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {&#xA;                copyTextToClipboard(editor.getValue())&#xA;                    .then(() =&gt; {&#xA;                        copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copied&#39;;&#xA;                        window.setTimeout(() =&gt; {&#xA;                            copyBtn.textContent = &#39;Copy&#39;;&#xA;                        }, 1200);&#xA;                    })&#xA;                    .catch((err) =&gt; {&#xA;                        console.error(&#39;Failed to copy source&#39;);&#xA;                        console.error(err);&#xA;                    });&#xA;            });&#xA;            function resizeAutoHeightEditor() {&#xA;                const lineHeight = editor.renderer.lineHeight || 21;&#xA;                const screenLines = Math.max(editor.session.getScreenLength(), 1);&#xA;                const nextHeight = Math.max(screenLines * lineHeight, 48);&#xA;&#xA;                editor.container.style.height = `${nextHeight}px`;&#xA;                editor.resize();&#xA;            }&#xA;&#xA;            editor.session.on(&#39;change&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            window.addEventListener(&#39;resize&#39;, resizeAutoHeightEditor);&#xA;            resizeAutoHeightEditor();&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;Name&lt;/code&gt; returns an identifier for logging and diagnostics. &lt;code&gt;Register&lt;/code&gt; receives a &lt;code&gt;Bootstrap&lt;/code&gt; context that provides access to the engine&amp;rsquo;s registries and hook system.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
